          "fix": "Change to: ((c2.financed_mt / (cls.financed || 1)) * 100).toFixed(1)"
        },
        {
          "severity": "P1",
          "line_approx": 363,
          "issue": "WACI values in seed data do not match spec formula WACI = financed_emissions / portfolio_value × 1,000,000",
          "detail": "Spec: WACI = financed_emissions / portfolio_value × 1,000,000 (per $M). Listed Equity: 8.48 MtCO₂e = 8,480,000 tCO₂e; outstanding=$4,200M; computed WACI = 8,480,000/4,200 = 2,019 tCO₂/$M. Displayed value: 68.4. The displayed WACI appears to be revenue-based (company revenues, not outstanding). The spec formula and displayed values are irreconcilable without a denominator correction.",
          "fix": "If WACI should be portfolio-level: recompute waci = (c.financed * 1e6) / c.outstanding. If revenue-based is intentional, label as 'Revenue WACI (tCO₂/$M revenue)' and add a note that this differs from PCAF portfolio WACI definition."
        },
        {
          "severity": "P1",
          "line_approx": 40,
          "issue": "Financed emissions formula includes full Scope 3 in EVIC attribution — non-standard",
          "detail": "formula string and calculation at line 265: attribution × (scope1 + scope2 + scope3). The PCAF Standard (v1.1 and v2.0) for listed equity/corporate bonds specifies attribution × (Scope 1 + Scope 2) as the primary method; full Scope 3 inclusion is an optional extension. Including all 14.62 Mt Scope 3 for Listed Equity inflates financed emissions above the standard baseline.",
          "fix": "Primary: financed = attribution × (scope1 + scope2). Optional separate disclosure: financed_with_S3 = attribution × (scope1 + scope2 + scope3). Update formula string and displayed calculation accordingly."
        },
