          "detail": "base2023 = c.trajectory.find(d=>d.year===2023)?.actual ?? c.trajectory[4]?.actual ?? 1. If actual 2023 data is missing and trajectory[4] is also null/undefined, fallback is 1. Then reduction2030 = ((1 - target2030val) / 1 * 100) which would render e.g. '-29900%' for BP (target2030=290, base=1: reduction = (1-290)/1*100 = -28900%). This would render a wildly wrong value to screen.",
          "fix": "const base2023 = c.trajectory.find(d => d.year === 2023 && d.actual != null)?.actual; const reduction2030 = (base2023 != null && base2023 > 0) ? (((base2023 - target2030val) / base2023) * 100).toFixed(0) : 'N/A';"
